<title>USA: Schwab unveils lower cost index mutual fund shrs.</title>
<headline>Schwab unveils lower cost index mutual fund shrs.</headline>
<dateline>SAN FRANCISCO 1997-05-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Charles Schwab &amp; Co. Inc Wednesday introduced Select Shares -- a new, lower-cost class of shares for each of the four index funds in the SchwabFunds family of mutual funds.</p>
<p>In a statement, Schwab said Select Shares require a minimum initial deposit of $50,000 and have operating expense ratios among the lowest in the mutual fund industry:</p>
<p>    Fund		     Select Shares OERs</p>
<p>    S&amp;P 500 Fund		    0.19%</p>
<p>    Schwab 1000 Index Fund	0.35%</p>
<p>    Small Cap Index Fund	  0.38%</p>
<p>    International Index Fund    0.47%</p>
